biggest by assets, said third quarter profit rose 19 percent
after it reduced the amount of funds set aside for loan
delinquencies.   Net income rose to 2.78 billion rupees ($32.4 million), or
2.28 rupees a share in the three months ended Sept. 30, from
2.34 billion rupees or 1.91 rupees a year earlier, the Karachi-
based company said in a filing to the stock exchange today.
Total income rose to 9.16 billion rupees from 7.99 billion.  Loan provisions fell to 1.86 billion rupees from 2.32
